<title>SINGAPORE: RESEARCH ALERT-Switch, don't sell Singapore shares.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT-Switch, don't sell Singapore shares.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1997-07-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Schroder Securities (S) Pte Ltd said on Wednesday it recommended a switch and not a sale of Singapore shares despite remaining cautious about the market.</p>
<p>In its July 16, 1997 report, the research house said it was not recommending a sell on the market despite the negative trends in the overall economy and the loss of the island-state's safe haven status as some stocks are now looking cheap.</p>
<p>&quot;Our yield-gap chart is actually giving a strong buy signal. Our strategy is therefore to switch and not sell because we still have stocks that we like,&quot; it said.  </p>
<p>Among the stocks recommended were electronic firms Acer Computer, Clipsal Industries and Venture Manufacturing.</p>
<p>Others included Courts, United Overseas Land and Keppel Corp.</p>
<p>-- Singapore newsroom (65 8703080)</p>
